The paper focuses on improving the performance of image classification tasks using deep convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new loss function, which falls under the sub-category of machine learning, cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the effectiveness of the proposed loss function on different types of image classification datasets, which could fall under the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also mentions experiments on large-scale image classification, which could fall under the sub-category of multimedia (cs.MM).
